<dl id="n11123d"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n11" href="#n11123d">N11 (VI.B.5)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n11all.htm#n11123d"> 123(d)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Albani (card) / faux par caract&egrave;re et franc / par humeur</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Le <mark>cardinal Albani est un homme d&apos;esprit, faux par caract&egrave;re et franc par humeur</mark>; sa violence d&eacute;joue sa ruse; on peut en tirer parti en flattant son orgueil et satisfaisant son avarice. <br><font color="green">[Cardinal Albani is a man whose spirit is dissembling by nature and outspoken when irritated; his violence foils his trickery; one could make use of this by flattering his pride and satisfying his greed.]</font> <small> Chateaubriand, <a name="CHBD" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#CHBD"><cite title="source">&OElig;uvres choisies illustr&eacute;es</cite></a> (1912) III, <i> M&eacute;moires d&apos;Outre-tombe.</i>140</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
